[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hugo Lloris: Tottenham Hotspur goalkeeper out for four weeks with hamstring injury

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Tottenham goalkeeper Hugo Lloris will be out for four weeks after suffering a hamstring injury during the 1-1 draw with Everton on Saturday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The French international was replaced by Michel Vorm after 35 minutes of the game at Goodison Park.
Spurs conceded after five minutes against Everton when Ross Barkley's free-kick sneaked past Lloris.
Lloris, 29, could miss Spurs' next four league games against Crystal Palace, Liverpool, Stoke and Sunderland.
